monaco-editor version: 0.8.3 in Chrome, I don't know which version VSCode uses
Browser: Chrome and VSCode as well
OS: Windows 10

The following less snippet is valid LESS but is marked as invalid:
```less
@sub-element: sub-element;
.my-element:not(.prefix-@{sub-element}) {
  color: red;
}
```
![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/9696261/26548571/1f91b45c-4475-11e7-9ecc-dcf062de54fb.png)


The monaco editor has the same behaviour (https://microsoft.github.io/monaco-editor/). As you can see here (http://less2css.org/#%7B%22less%22%3A%22%20%20%40sub-element%3A%20sub-element%3B%5Cn%20%20.my-element%3Anot(.prefix-%40%7Bsub-element%7D)%20%7B%5Cn%20%20%20%20color%3A%20red%3B%5Cn%20%20%7D%22%7D) the LESS is valid and compiles to valid CSS

